&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mission: e&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--font-style-italic&quot;&gt;liminating&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;every barrier to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--accent-1-color&quot;&gt;mental health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring Health is a global mental health company on a mission to eliminate every barrier to mental health. We&#39;re building a world where getting support is simple, personal, and built around the person, so care can continue through every job, move, health plan, and life stage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our AI-native platform helps us deliver personalized support across self-guided tools, coaching, therapy, medication management, and specialty care. With outcomes independently validated by JAMA Network Open and the Validation Institute, Spring Health reaches more than 170 million people worldwide through leading employers, health plans, and partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an AI-native company, we believe technology should expand the reach, quality, and humanity of care. Every Spring Health team member is expected to use AI tools thoughtfully, apply human judgment to AI outputs, and keep building AI fluency in ways that support their role and our mission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Account Executives in our Commercial Sales team are focused on companies with under 10,000 employees.You will lead the full sales cycle from prospecting to close, driving new business and building strong client relationships. This role includes managing RFPs, leading discovery calls, and delivering tailored presentations that showcase our value. You will collaborate with internal teams and external partners to expand revenue and achieve quota goals while representing our solutions with expertise and confidence. This is a full-time position on our team, reporting to one of the Commercial Sales Leaders. Occasional travel may be required for team or company events.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have four levels of AEs in our Commercial team:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commercial Account Executive (AE1) - under 750 employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Senior Commercial Account Executive (AE2) - 750-2000 employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mid Market Account Executive (AE3) - 2000-5000 employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Senior Mid Market Account Executive (AE4) - 5000-10,000 employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;While we don&#39;t have an active opening for this role right now, but we&#39;re building a pipeline of AEs for our Commercial team for when we do. If this sounds like you, we&#39;d love to stay connected!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Not sure if you meet every requirement?&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://pubsonline.informs.org/doi/10.1287/mnsc.2023.4907&quot;&gt;Research shows&lt;/a&gt; that women and people from historically underrepresented communities often hesitate to apply for roles unless they meet every qualification compared to other similarly-qualified candidates. At Spring Health, we are committed to fostering a workplace where everyone feels valued, empowered, and supported to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.springhealth.com/careers&quot;&gt;Thrive&lt;/a&gt;. If this role excites you, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Our privacy policy:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://springhealth.com/privacy-policy/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;https://springhealth.com/privacy-policy/&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Spring Health is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate in hiring or any employment decision based on race, color, religion, national origin, age, sex, marital status, ancest

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mission: e&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--font-style-italic&quot;&gt;liminating&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;every barrier to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--accent-1-color&quot;&gt;mental health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring Health is a global mental health company on a mission to eliminate every barrier to mental health. We&#39;re building a world where getting support is simple, personal, and built around the person, so care can continue through every job, move, health plan, and life stage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our AI-native platform helps us deliver personalized support across self-guided tools, coaching, therapy, medication management, and specialty care. With outcomes independently validated by JAMA Network Open and the Validation Institute, Spring Health reaches more than 170 million people worldwide through leading employers, health plans, and partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an AI-native company, we believe technology should expand the reach, quality, and humanity of care. Every Spring Health team member is expected to use AI tools thoughtfully, apply human judgment to AI outputs, and keep building AI fluency in ways that support their role and our mission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Senior Director of Customer Success and partnering closely with Sales, Renewals, and cross-functional teams, the Associate Director, Customer Success will lead a team of Customer Success Managers responsible for the health, retention, and growth of Spring Health’s Commercial and SMB customer segments. This is a full-time, fully remote position. The ideal candidate would be able to work CST or EST hours. Travel to our NYC headquarters is required quarterly.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and develop a team of Customer Success Managers supporting the Commercial and SMB book of business, setting clear goals and holding the team accountable to outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the health and retention of the Commercial &amp;amp; SMB portfolio, using account health signals to prioritize where the team spends its time each week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run a recurring risk and renewal review cadence, ensuring every at-risk account has a clear, documented action plan and owner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales, Renewals, and Deal Desk to manage upcoming renewals and expansion opportunities across the segment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate customer feedback and escalation trends into clear recommendations for Product, Support, and other cross-functional partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize playbooks, onboarding, and account planning practices across the CSM team to improve consistency and support scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report on segment-level performance to CS leadership, flagging risk and opportunity trends early.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hire, onboard, and ramp new CSMs as the team grows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion consistent, accurate use of CS systems and tools so account data stays current and actionable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the voice of the customer in cross-functional planning and strategy discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What success looks like:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Net/gross revenue retention targets met or exceeded for the Commercial &amp;amp; SMB book.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quarter-over-quarter reduction in at-risk account exposure within the segment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High renewal timeliness — the majority of renewals close on or before contract end date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer satisfaction (CSAT/NPS) scores across the segment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Healthy CSM team retention and consistent ramp time for new hires.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mission: e&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--font-style-italic&quot;&gt;liminating&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;every barrier to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--accent-1-color&quot;&gt;mental health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring Health is a global mental health company on a mission to eliminate every barrier to mental health. We&#39;re building a world where getting support is simple, personal, and built around the person, so care can continue through every job, move, health plan, and life stage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our AI-native platform helps us deliver personalized support across self-guided tools, coaching, therapy, medication management, and specialty care. With outcomes independently validated by JAMA Network Open and the Validation Institute, Spring Health reaches more than 170 million people worldwide through leading employers, health plans, and partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an AI-native company, we believe technology should expand the reach, quality, and humanity of care. Every Spring Health team member is expected to use AI tools thoughtfully, apply human judgment to AI outputs, and keep building AI fluency in ways that support their role and our mission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Senior Director, Strategic Operations, the Associate Director of Strategic Operations will focus on driving operational rigor, scalability, and gross margin expansion across the business. This leader will be embedded within the operations organization but partner closely with Finance, Product, Revenue, Clinical, and Customer teams to improve how we deliver care - ensuring we do so efficiently, sustainably, and at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is deeply execution-oriented. In addition to identifying high-impact efficiency opportunities, this person will serve as the programmatic owner of large, cross-functional initiatives - ensuring teams remain aligned, accountable, and on track to deliver measurable outcomes. Unlike traditional business strategy roles that focus on market expansion or new growth vectors, this role is centered on optimizing the core: improving unit economics, strengthening operational performance, and building durable systems that unlock long-term profitability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid role based in New York City, with an expectation to be in office 2-3 days a week. Our office is located at 60 Madison Avenue. Additionally, occasional travel may be required for company or team events.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategy: Lead strategic operational efficiency initiatives by diagnosing workflow, system, and cross-functional inefficiencies and designing scalable solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI Leverage: Identify and evaluate opportunities to leverage AI and automation to improve operational efficiency, reduce cost-to-serve, and enhance scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial Ownership: Translate margin targets into actionable operational initiatives with clear owners, timelines, and measurable KPIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Program Leadership: Own complex, cross-functional programs across Operations and adjacent teams (Product, Revenue, Finance, Clinical).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Governance: Establish governance structures, milestones, and success metrics to ensure initiatives are delivered on time and at impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business Case Development: Build business cases for automation, tooling improvements, vendor optimization, and process redesign.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;KPI Rigor: Connect financial targets to day-to-day operations through performance dashboards, KPI rigor, and accountability cadences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success Looks Like in This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-functional programs executed with strong stakeholder alignment and m

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mission: e&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--font-style-italic&quot;&gt;liminating&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;every barrier to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--accent-1-color&quot;&gt;mental health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring Health is a global mental health company on a mission to eliminate every barrier to mental health. We&#39;re building a world where getting support is simple, personal, and built around the person, so care can continue through every job, move, health plan, and life stage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our AI-native platform helps us deliver personalized support across self-guided tools, coaching, therapy, medication management, and specialty care. With outcomes independently validated by JAMA Network Open and the Validation Institute, Spring Health reaches more than 170 million people worldwide through leading employers, health plans, and partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an AI-native company, we believe technology should expand the reach, quality, and humanity of care. Every Spring Health team member is expected to use AI tools thoughtfully, apply human judgment to AI outputs, and keep building AI fluency in ways that support their role and our mission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Director of Operations Analytics &amp;amp; Workforce Optimization, the Business Analyst, Operations Analytics will drive the strategic analytics work for cross-cutting, operations-wide priorities—some of the most critical initiatives in the department. This role sits on the Operations Analytics team within Operations Intelligence and will serve as a high-leverage analytics partner to Operations leadership, helping define what “good” looks like, how we measure it, and how we improve it. This is a full time, fully-remote position, though the ability to be onsite in our NYC office once a week is preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will have two primary categories of work:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strategic analytics for Ops-wide initiatives:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide the strategic analytics horsepower for major, cross-functional Operations initiatives (e.g., AI transformation efforts) by framing ambiguous problems, identifying decision-critical metrics, and driving analyses that directly shape strategy and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex analytics into clear, actionable recommendations for Operations leadership, leveraging AI functionality wherever possible to reduce time-to-insight and increase actionability.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build decision-ready narratives for exec audiences: clear problem statements, crisp insights, quantified tradeoffs, and recommended actions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally (Operations leaders, BI, Product, and other stakeholders) to ensure analytics work is connected to real operational levers and adopted in day-to-day decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ops-wide analytics + performance measurement foundation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the creation of core data and reporting groundwork that ensures Operations understands what should be measured, how it’s measured, and how we’re performing.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver foundational assets such as:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An Operations-wide metrics dictionary (definitions, logic, ownership, refresh cadence, caveats).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recurring Operations performance packages that surface the most critical business metrics and trends.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Metric trees that enable faster, more systematic root-cause analysis when performance shifts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with leaders across each Operations department and BI partners to align on metric definitions, ensure data quality, and maintain scalable reporting.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mission: e&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--font-style-italic&quot;&gt;liminating&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;every barrier to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--accent-1-color&quot;&gt;mental health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
