&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead short-term frontline team members’ scheduling efforts, including weekly shift planning, intra- and inter-day changes, and RTA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and monitor key performance metrics such as adherence, occupancy, and shrinkage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI and broader automation tools to maximize the quality of your output and the efficiency of your work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex analytics into actionable insights to drive operational efficiency and resourcing decisions, leveraging AI functionality wherever possible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a strategic partner to Care Operations leadership, providing guidance on resourcing decisions and capacity planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key liaison for Care Operations workforce optimization in cross-functional initiatives, collaborating with teams such as Product, Marketing, and Customer Success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What success looks like:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Workforce management plan adherence: Strong alignment and adherence to workforce management plans across the Care Operations teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Care Operations SLAs: Improved SLA performance metrics (e.g., time to first reply, time to resolution) attributed to your scheduling work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Workflow efficiency: Reduce time and effort required to run recurring workforce processes through AI and automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal partner satisfaction: Care Operations leadership views you as a trusted strategic partner, not just an analytics provider&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Business, Economics, Engineering, or a similar analytical field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2-3 years of experience in operations strategy, analytics, or a related role (e.g., management

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mission: e&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--font-style-italic&quot;&gt;liminating&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;every barrier to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;heading--accent-1-color&quot;&gt;mental health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring Health is a global mental health company on a mission to eliminate every barrier to mental health. We&#39;re building a world where getting support is simple, personal, and built around the person, so care can continue through every job, move, health plan, and life stage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our AI-native platform helps us deliver personalized support across self-guided tools, coaching, therapy, medication management, and specialty care. With outcomes independently validated by JAMA Network Open and the Validation Institute, Spring Health reaches more than 170 million people worldwide through leading employers, health plans, and partners.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an AI-native company, we believe technology should expand the reach, quality, and humanity of care. Every Spring Health team member is expected to use AI tools thoughtfully, apply human judgment to AI outputs, and keep building AI fluency in ways that support their role and our mission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: We don&#39;t have an active opening for this role right now, but we&#39;re building a pipeline of BDRs in New York City for when we do. If this sounds like you, we&#39;d love to stay connected!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Business Development Representative (BDR) is responsible for building and maintaining an excellent working relationship with our Marketing and Account Executives. This position will be a major change agent at Spring Health, having impact and influence with a high degree of autonomy and flexibility. The ideal candidate enjoys testing and learning to ultimately become an effective seller and leader. In addition, we are seeking creative and passionate individuals eager to develop their skill sets to be successful long term in their careers who believe in honesty and transparency. This is a 40-hour-per-week, hourly (non-exempt) role with a standard schedule of 8:30 AM – 5:00 PM (includes a 30-minute unpaid lunch break), Monday through Friday. In-office days are Mondays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays for the BDR team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: This position requires working out of our NYC office 3x a week at 60 Madison Ave.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop outreach strategy, content, in-bound lead process, and development programs for the BDR team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospect into Fortune 1000 companies and other employers through a combination of email, phone call, and other sales channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate sales-ready meetings and opportunities for Account Executive using Spring Health’s qualification criteria&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide accurate lead distribution and thorough discovery to the assigned Account Executive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop all of the critical skills to accelerate a successful career in Sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What success looks like in this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You achieve your targets for qualified meetings and opportunities pipeline as set out for each quarter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You successfully complete all assigned trainings and continuously improve your sales skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You collaborate effectively with your team, leaders, and cross-functional peers to drive success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You demonstrate persistence and creativity in reaching decision-makers and generating interest in Spring Health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You proactively seek feedback and opportunities for improvement to refine your outreach strategies and tactics.

